Assignment name  : add_digits
Expected files   : add_digits.c
Allowed functions: write
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Write a function that takes a string representing a positive number and
displays its digital sum, followed by a newline.

The digital sum is obtained by adding all digits of the number. If the result
has more than one digit, repeat the process until a single digit is obtained.

You can assume that the string will only contain digit characters.

If the number of parameters is not 1, the program displays a newline.

Examples:

$> ./add_digits "42" | cat -e
6$
$> ./add_digits "9999" | cat -e
9$
$> ./add_digits "12345" | cat -e
6$
$> ./add_digits | cat -e
$
